              Name of existing sites file.

       vveecctt==_n_a_m_e
              Name of the output file (binary vector file).


       s.hull can be run either non-interactively or interactively.  The  pro-
       gram will be run non-interactively if the user specifies the name of an
       existing site list file and a name for a vect file, using the form
                  s.hull [-a] sites=name1 vect=name2

       where  name1 is the name of an existing site list file and name2 is the
       name of vector output file.


       Alternately,  the  user  can  simply     type   s.hull   on   the  com-
       mand   line,  without program arguments.  In this case, the  user  will
       be    prompted    for   parameter   values    using    the   standard
       GRASS    parser    interface described in the manual entry for  parser.
       In either case,  v.support should  be  run on the output (the "-s" flag
       can be used for that).

